## Example 2 — Simplify Using Absolute Value

When you find an even root of an even power and the result is an odd power, use absolute value to keep the principal root nonnegative.

### a. `fourthroot(81x^4)`

`= fourthroot((3x)^4) = 3|x|`

### b. `eighthroot(256(y^2 - 2)^24)`

`= eighthroot(256) * eighthroot((y^2 - 2)^24)`

`= 2 |(y^2 - 2)^3|`

## Talk About It

