## Example 3 — Radical and Exponential Forms

Simplify.

### a. Write `x^(4/3)` in radical form

`x^(4/3) = cuberoot(x^4)`

### b. Write `fifthroot(x^2)` in exponential form

`fifthroot(x^2) = x^(2/5)`

