## Example 4 — Use Rational Exponents

The expression `c(1 + r)^t` estimates future cost due to inflation.

Write the expression in radical form for an item `3` months from now if the annual inflation rate is `4.7%`.

Since `3` months is `1/4` year:

`c(1 + r)^t = c(1 + 0.047)^(1/4)`

`= c(1.047)^(1/4)`

`= c * fourthroot(1.047)`

## Think About It

Why did you set `t = 1/4`?

