## Example 5 — Evaluate Expressions with Rational Exponents

Evaluate:

`32^(-2/5)`

`= 1 / 32^(2/5)`

`= 1 / (2^5)^(2/5)`

`= 1 / 2^2`

`= 1/4`

---

## Example 6 — Simplify Expressions with Rational Exponents

### a. `x^(2/3) * x^(1/6)`

`= x^(2/3 + 1/6)`

`= x^(4/6 + 1/6)`

`= x^(5/6)`

### b. `y^(-2/3)`

`= 1 / y^(2/3)`

### c. `z^(-1/3) * z^(3/4)`

`= z^(-1/3 + 3/4)`

`= z^(-4/12 + 9/12)`

`= z^(5/12)`

